What is Routing in Node.js?

Routing is the process of defining how a server responds to different URLs (endpoints) and HTTP methods.

👉 Simple:

URL + Method → Decide what code runs
🎯 Example
GET /home     → Show homepage
POST /login   → Handle login
⚙️ 2️⃣ Routing using Core Node.js (http module)
💻 Basic Example
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {

    if (req.url === '/' && req.method === 'GET') {
        res.end("Home Page");
    }

    else if (req.url === '/about' && req.method === 'GET') {
        res.end("About Page");
    }

    else if (req.url === '/login' && req.method === 'POST') {
        res.end("Login Successful");
    }

    else {
        res.statusCode = 404;
        res.end("Page Not Found");
    }
});

server.listen(3000);
